Anglo American Applies to Extend Life of Drayton Coal Mine, Australia Says

-- B y   E l i s a b e t h   B e h r m a n n
-- 
2011-04-11T06:29:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/anglo-american-applies-to-extend-life-of-drayton-coal-mine-australia-says.html
Anglo American Plc (AAL)  applied to
extend the Drayton open-cut  coal mine  in New South Wales state
to build an operation capable of delivering 7 million metric
tons of thermal coal annually over a 26-year period, the
Department of Sustainability, Environment, Water, Population and
Communities said in a notice on its website. Coal reserves at
the existing Drayton mine are expected to run out in 2015.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisabeth Behrmann in Sydney at 
 ebehrmann1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Victoria Batchelor at 
 vbatchelor@bloomberg.net  